---
/**
 * production-ai-architecture/0001 · Figure 4 (Module 2) — capacity is the token, and
 * the ceiling is upstream: requests queue behind a provider token-per-minute limit.
 *
 * Verbatim copy of the source SVG (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote
 * <sup> #s3 / id="r3b"). References the shared #arw and #arwG markers from
 * Defs.astro.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Requests queue behind a fixed provider token-per-minute limit; long-output requests consume the budget and cause head-of-line blocking, so admission control and per-tenant budgets are needed before the limit."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >You queue behind a token limit you don't own</text
        >
        <!-- incoming -->
        <rect x="24" y="56" width="92" height="26" rx="5" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="70" y="73" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">short request</text>
        <rect x="24" y="92" width="92" height="26" rx="5" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="70" y="109" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >long-output job</text
        >
        <rect x="24" y="128" width="92" height="26" rx="5" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="70" y="145" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">short request</text
        >
        <!-- admission control -->
        <line x1="116" y1="105" x2="150" y2="105" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect
            x="152"
            y="78"
            width="120"
            height="56"
            rx="8"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="212" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Admission control</text
        >
        <text x="212" y="115" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >per-tenant token budget</text
        >
        <text x="212" y="127" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >+ queue + shed</text
        >
        <!-- the limit wall -->
        <line
            x1="300"
            y1="40"
            x2="300"
            y2="170"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="2.5"
            stroke-dasharray="6 4"></line>
        <text x="300" y="184" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >provider rate limit</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >tokens / min · you don't set it</text
        >
        <line x1="272" y1="105" x2="297" y2="105" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <!-- model -->
        <rect
            x="356"
            y="78"
            width="120"
            height="56"
            rx="8"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="416" y="103" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Model</text
        >
        <text x="416" y="118" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >cost &amp; latency scale</text
        >
        <text x="416" y="129" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >with output length</text
        >
        <line x1="303" y1="105" x2="354" y2="105" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <!-- self-host note -->
        <rect x="500" y="62" width="120" height="88" rx="8" fill="#f6f4ef" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="560" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >If self-hosted</text
        >
        <text x="560" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f">the wall is</text>
        <text x="560" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >KV-cache memory</text
        >
        <text x="560" y="128" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >grows: context len</text
        >
        <text x="560" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >&times; concurrency</text
        >
        <line
            x1="476"
            y1="106"
            x2="498"
            y2="106"
            stroke="#6b675f"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="24" y="206" width="592" height="34" rx="6" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="227" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >&#9888; No admission control &rarr; one long-output job consumes the budget and
            head-of-line-blocks everyone &rarr; latency cliff, not graceful slowdown.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Model it as a queue with a token budget and a hard upstream ceiling. Capacity planning here
        is the AI analogue of connection-pool and thread-pool sizing — get it wrong and you get a
        latency cliff, not a gentle slowdown.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r3b">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
